Setup Instructions
Prerequisites
Before running the app, ensure you have the following installed:

Node.js (v14 or higher)

Step 1: Clone the Repository
Clone the repository to your local machine:

bash
Copy
git clone https://github.com/your-username/quiz-app.git
cd quiz-app
Step 2: Install Dependencies
Install the required dependencies for the project:

bash
Copy
npm install

Step 3: Set Up the Backend (Optional)
If you want to use your own backend API:

Set up a backend server (e.g., using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB).

Update the API endpoints in the Quiz.js and Leaderboard.js files to point to your backend.

For example, replace:

javascript
Copy
axios.get("http://localhost:5000/api");
with your backend URL:

javascript
Copy
axios.get("https://your-backend-url/api");
Step 4: Run the App
Start the development server:

bash
Copy
npm start
The app will be available at http://localhost:3000.

Step 5: Build for Production
To build the app for production:

bash
Copy
npm run build
The production-ready files will be generated in the build folder.
